<Meta title="Helpers/Directives/Row gap/Guide" />

# Row gap

This directive allows you to add the `row-gap` CSS property using Canopy spacing.
The spacing variables are also available as CSS custom properties (CSS variables)
which can be viewed in **_canopy/projects/canopy/src/styles/spacing.scss_**.

This directive and accompanying CSS classes, work great with our
[Canopy grid](./?path=/docs/helpers-directives-grid-guide--docs) but will
also work with all other HTML elements that support <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/row-gap" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CSS row-gap</a>.

## Usage

Import the row gap directive in your application:

```js
  imports: [ ..., LgRowGapDirective ]
```

### Examples

Apply `8` row-gap.

```html
<div lgRowGap="8"></div>
```

Use the default (`4`) row-gap.

```html
<div lgRowGap></div>
```

## Inputs

The current available spacing variants are:

<pre>
  <code className="language-text">
    {(() => {
      const spacingVars = getDefaultSpacingVariables();
      const variants = Object.keys(spacingVars)
        .filter((key) => key.startsWith('--space-'))
        .map((key) => key.replace('--space-', ''))
        .sort((a, b) => {
          // Handle 'none' specially
          if (a === 'none') return -1;
          if (b === 'none') return 1;
          // Sort numbers numerically
          return parseInt(a) - parseInt(b);
        })
        .map((variant) => `'${variant}'`)
        .join(', ');

      return `'none', ${variants}`;
    })()}
  </code>
</pre>

| Name       | Description                                |       Type       | Default | Required |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------ | :--------------: | :-----: | :------: |
| `lgRowGap` | The row gap variant applied to the element | `SpacingVariant` |   `4`   |   Yes    |

---

